X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Campuslabs Montclair": "https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12347607"}
X-SOURCE-ID:campuslabs_montclair
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Academic/Educational
DESCRIPTION:The College of Humanities and Social Sciences is launching a n
 ew AI Distinguished Speaker Series—a yearlong exploration of how artifici
 al intelligence is reshaping human systems\, knowledge\, and society. Des
 igned to be inclusive and engaging\, the series will bring thought leader
 s to campus who not only explain emerging technologies but also invite st
 udents and the wider community into critical conversations about their im
 pact. By blending expert insight with student-centered formats\, the seri
 es aims to spark new ways of learning\, questioning\, and participating i
 n AI’s future.\nThe AI-Ready Campus: From Pockets of Innovation to a Cohe
 rent Institutional Strategy\nAcross higher education\, the adoption of ge
 nerative AI has been rapid and revolutionary. While many faculty and staf
 f are exploring these powerful new tools\, this energy is often siloed\, 
 leading to a campus of “AI pockets” rather than a truly AI-ready institut
 ion. The next great challenge is moving from this phase of enthusiastic b
 ut fragmented experimentation to one of deliberate\, strategic\, and holi
 stic integration. How do we build an institutional AI strategy that is mo
 re than just a collection of policies and tools?\nRegister to Attend\n\nH
 osted by: College of Humanities and Social Sciences (CHSS)\n\nAdditional 
 Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/even
 t/12347607
DTEND:20260401T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043556Z
DTSTART:20260401T140000Z
LOCATION:Presentation Hall\, College of Communication and Media
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:AI Distinguished Speaker Series: The AI-Ready Campus: From Pockets
  of Innovation to a Coherent Institutional Strategy
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12347607
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12347607
X-HOSTS:College of Humanities and Social Sciences (CHSS)
END:VEVENT
