 nds-on program invites participants of all ages to explore a variety of d
 ecorating techniques—from classic dyeing to modern\, imaginative designs.
 \nDuring the session\, guests can experiment with:\n\n\nVibrant dyes and 
 color blends\n\n\nStickers\, stencils\, and decorative tapes\n\n\nPaints\
 , markers\, and metallic accents\n\n\nNatural dye options for an eco-frie
 ndly twist\n\n\nCreative themes like animals\, patterns\, characters\, an
 d abstract art\n\n\n \nLocation - Bloomfield Campus: Franklin Hall - 460 
 Franklin Street\, Bloomfield\, NJ 07003 [Third Floor - Multipurpose Room 
 (MPR) - Room 314]\n\nHosted by: Bloomfield's Office of Residence Life\n\n
