BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Campuslabs Montclair": "https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12358876"}
X-SOURCE-ID:campuslabs_montclair
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
DESCRIPTION:Many Latino professionals are navigating spaces our families w
 ere never given access to-learning workplace norms\, financial literacy\,
  and career strategies without the benefit of generational guidance. For 
 those who come from low-income or historically underserved communities\, 
 success often means figuring out systems that were never designed with us
  in mind.\nThis conversation explores what it means to be first-generatio
 n professionals\, to build skills and stability that we may not have inhe
 rited\, and to confront the pressure to assimilate in order to succeed Mo
 re importantly\, it asks: how do we grow in corporate and professional sp
 aces without losing our identity\, our community\, and the values that sh
 aped us?\nJoin us for an honest discussion on navigating professional env
 ironments\, closing generational knowledge gaps\, building financial and 
 career confidence\, and staying rooted in culture while advancing in spac
 es where representation is still growing. This event is about redefining 
 success-not as leaving where we come from behind\, but as carrying it wit
 h us as we create new pathways for those who will follow.\n\nHosted by: S
 igma Lambda Beta International Fraternity Inc.\n\nAdditional Information 
 can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12358876
DTEND:20260402T023000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043556Z
DTSTART:20260402T003000Z
LOCATION:University Hall 1020 - Bard-Blount Family Lecture Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Sin Olvidar: Climbing Ladders\, Carrying Culture
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12358876
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12358876
X-HOSTS:Sigma Lambda Beta International Fraternity Inc.
END:VEVENT
