SUMMARY:Jazz film screening: Soundtrack to a Coup d'Etat
DESCRIPTION:Johan Grimonprez's 2025 Oscar nominee for Best Documentary 
 Feature dives deep into the complex history of the Democratic Republic of 
 Congo\, exploring the turbulent events behind the rise and fall of Patrice 
 Lumumba\, its first elected prime minister. From his 1961 assassination to 
 Max Roach and Abbey Lincoln crashing the UN Security Council\, Soundtrack 
 to a Coup d'Etat reveals the covert dynamics of power and resistance that 
 shaped Congo and the world stage. Powerful and moving.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-10306-16269261
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16269261
END:VEVENT
