SUMMARY:Make a Peacock Mandala NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register on 
 the Adult School website.\n\nA mandala (Sanskrit for “circle”) is an 
 artistic representation of higher thought and deeper meaning expressed as a 
 geometric symbol and used to focus one's attention. The peacock is the 
 national bird of India\, and in this class\, participants will learn how to 
 use acrylic paint\, rods and metal balls of different sizes\, and tiny 
 mirrors on a 10" wooden round to create a beautiful\, dimensional image of 
 the bird. All materials included.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15826227
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15826227
END:VEVENT
