SUMMARY:Tales on the Trails - Beauty of Trees
DESCRIPTION:Tales on the Trails \nWednesdays\, 1:00 PM -1:45 PM \nAge: Preschool 3-5 year olds \nApril 8th – Beauty of Trees \nApril’s Tales on the Trails class is all about trees. Learn about trees\, their leaves\, and the important role they play in our gardens. \nDiscover the wonders of the outdoor world with your little one.  This program begins in the gardens of Van Vleck with a story\, then continues with a walk and concludes with a simple craft or activity.  All programs focus on the theme listed.  A parent or caregiver must accompany each child.  Programs will be held outdoors\, weather permitting. \nSponsored by The Albert Payson Terhune Foundation  \nFee: $10/class per child for Members / $15/class per child for General Public \nRegistration required by 1 day prior to each class \n \n  \nUpcoming Classes \nMay 27th – Sounds of Spring \nDo you hear the birds singing\, the wind blowing\, and rabbits scurrying around? These are all the sounds of spring. Join us for Tales on the Trails as we use our senses to explore the wonders of spring. \n  \nJune 17th – Magic of Moths \nWhat’s flying around the gardens? Is it a butterfly or could it be a moth? Learn about moths at this month’s Tales on the Trails. 
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/tales-on-the-trails-beauty-of-trees/
CATEGORIES:Classes,Children
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2025/12/Art-Nature-Day-5-e1770313444529.jpg
END:VEVENT
