X-SOURCE:Libcal Bccls 10306
DTSTART:20260409T220000Z
DTEND:20260409T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260409T000000Z
SUMMARY:Jazz Library listening session: Sam Rivers
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a dive into the music and life of a true creative 
 force in modern jazz\, Sam Rivers. Brilliant multi-instrumentalist\, 
 composer\, heart of the New York jazz loft scene in the 1970s. Seed Artists 
 founder Pheeroan akLaff\, a colleague of Rivers\, will guide us through the 
 music\, share stories\, and pull excerpts from Rick Lopez's remarkable 
 768-page masterwork\, Sam Rivers Sessionography: A Work in Progress. We 
 listen. We talk. We listen some more. This event will be held on the first 
 floor\, Plymouth Street side.
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-10306-16316751
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16316751
END:VEVENT
