CATEGORIES:Academic/Educational
DESCRIPTION:Join the History Club for a full-day trip to Philadelphia as w
 e explore some of the most historic places in the United States.\nWe’ll v
 isit Independence Hall and the Liberty Bell\, followed by stops at the Mu
 seum of the American Revolution and the National Constitution Center. Tog
 ether\, these sites tell the story of the nation’s founding. We'll learn 
 about the debates and ideals that shaped the country and how those ideas 
 have been interpreted\, challenged\, and expanded over time.\nThis trip i
 s an opportunity to reflect on the past 250 years of American history whi
 le also thinking about the kind of country we hope to build in the next 2
 50.\nTo wrap up the day\, we’ll head to Dave and Buster’s to relax\, grab
  dinner\, and spend time together before returning home.\nThis trip is pa
 rt of Montclair State University’s Montclair 250 celebrations.\n\nHosted 
 by: The Historical Society at Montclair State\n\nAdditional Information c
 an be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12377877
DTEND:20260412T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043556Z
