SUMMARY:Daytime Pool at Clifton Billiards
DESCRIPTION:North Jersey Bowling\, Volleyball\, Tennis And More (BVT)\n***
 Trying something different this time\, Saturday afternoon date and in the 
 window for day passes! So if you are available and feel like staying longe
 r\, or coming closer to the middle or end\, it's more flexible\, easier to
  change between tables and play with more people and less time is spent co
 unting hours\, etc. We'll see how this pans out going forward.***\n\n***Me
 eting Point:***\nOutside of the building\; After 5-10 minutes: You can mee
 t us upstairs at the pool tables. *\\*\\*Please look for the group as the 
 staff do not keep up with the group\\*\\***\n*** Price:\nPhoto of the day 
 passes pricing is posted\, however if you only want to stay a short while 
 and would rather pay less\, the price is $6.50 per hour per person if you 
 have 4 players at your table. However\, the final price is based on the to
 tal amount of minutes played. At the end of the hour\, the table amount wi
 ll be split per person. Each table paying this way should have a table lea
 der\, **this person will collect the money of players at their table and w
 ill pay for the table on one card.** 3-4 table leaders will be needed\, **
 volunteering for this is encouraged**\n\n***Bringing cash is highly encour
 aged to pay your portion to your table leader***\n\n*Parking*: street park
 ing is available however it may be hard to find close to the venue. There 
 are side streets before the town proper\, but a good option is the nearby 
 ANT bookstore which has a lot which should be okay to use.\n\n***This loca
 tion has food & drinks available for purchase.***\n\n*** Expectations**:\n
 Pool cues are available at the location\, expect mid to low lighting. If y
 ou come after 7:15pm\, look for the Meetup group upstairs.\n** *What if I'
 m a beginner or only want to play with people at a similar level?**\nTable
 s will be divided between beginners\, intermediate players\, and advanced.
  However\, this depends on how many types of players come\, so it will be 
 divided as best as possibly available. If you would like game rules\, plea
 se speak with Marc.** Marc is also available to answer questions including
  how to hold the cue\, stances\, etc.**\n*** Is anyone at Clifton Billiard
 s after the event is over?\nAfterward\, most go home or go to a local bar.
  If you'd like to hang out after\, definitely speak with members to see if
  they want to do something after.\n*** Can I switch tables?**\n*Yes\, but 
 it does make it easier if you stay at your table. If you switch tables\, p
 ay the amount of time you were at that table. Example\, if you were at abl
 e A for an hour\, pay the hour to the table A leader. If you go table B fo
 r two hours\, pay your two hours to the table B leader. At the end\, the t
 able leader is taking the payments for the total amount of time at that ta
 ble.*\n*** How do I get balls for the table and how many people do I tell 
 staff that I have?*\n*One person per table gives their ID to the staff in 
 order to check out balls. Again\, the price for 4 people is about $6.50. I
 f you have more or less\, it slightly changes. So it just depends on how m
 any people are at your table. It may be better to mention that you have mo
 re people esp if you are starting with 4 or 5 people.*\n*** I feel like pe
 ople aren't trying to be my friend.*\n*Please remember that different peop
 le have different goals. Some may come to just play billiards\, others may
  be there to meet new people or do something social\, and some may be ther
 e to make long term friends. Find people that match your goals or be ok wi
 th others that may not.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleybal
 l/events/313908503/
