DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T120000
DTSTAMP:20260401T003536
CREATED:20260325T160916Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260325T160917Z
UID:10006616-1776164400-1776168000@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Mindfulness in the Garden - Early Spring Series
DESCRIPTION:Mindfulness in the Garden (Weekday Series) \nInstructor: Jodi Brooks \nTuesdays\, 11:00 AM – 12:00 PM \nEarly Spring Session: Apr 7\, 14\, & 28 (No class 4/21) \nDiscover how a mindfulness practice can help us awaken and  live in harmony with oneself and with the natural world. This class will include: simple instructions for getting started with a formal mindfulness practice\, very gentle stretching & breathwork\, and an outdoor contemplative garden walk. This is a practice of slowing down\, cultivating quiet and paying attention to our senses. All levels are welcome. No experience needed. Winter session will be held indoors\, with a short walk outdoors (weather permitting). \nFee: 3 April classes: General public $75\, Members $60 \nSeries registration only. Pre Registration is required – there are no drop-ins for this class. \n \nLate Spring Session: May 5\, 12 19 & 26 \nEarly Summer Session: June 2\, 9\, 16 & 23
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/mindfulness-early-spring-series-4/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/02/20250909_110531-scaled-e1774454912965.jpg
END:VEVENT
