DTSTART:20260414T171500Z
DTEND:20260414T181500Z
DTSTAMP:20260414T000000Z
SUMMARY:Everything Book Club\, "Happiness" by Aminatta Forna
DESCRIPTION:A meditation in fiction on love\, trauma\, chance\, and the 
 nature of wild things--perfect for Earth Day. A Ghanaian psychiatrist and 
 an American biologist who studies urban foxes bump into each other on 
 Waterloo Bridge in London and their fates entwine when they get involved in 
 a search for a missing boy. By a Scottish and Sierra Leonean writer whose 
 books have been translated into 22 languages.  \n\n“An exquisite novel 
 about how chance and love connect us.”—The Washington Post\n\nAminatta 
 Forna is a Scottish and Sierra Leonean writer whose books have been 
 translated into 22 languages. She spent periods of her childhood in Iran\, 
 Thailand and Zambia. She is also the author of three other novels\, 
 including "The Memory of Love" as well as two works of non-fiction. She is 
 a Fellow of the Royal Society of Literature
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Tower Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Book Discussion
UID:LibCal-10306-15933313
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15933313
END:VEVENT
