SUMMARY:Home Repair Essentials NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register. 
 \n\nLearn the fundamentals of home repair in this practical\, hands-on 
 workshop taught by Robert Haas\, instructor of the popular Woodworking 101 
 and Advanced Woodworking classes. Held at Montclair High School\, this 
 course gives participants a behind-the-walls look at how common home 
 features are built and maintained.\n\nDuring the class\, Robert will 
 construct two demonstration walls that include doors and a window\, showing 
 how these elements are installed and how typical wall structures are 
 assembled. Participants will also learn how traditional double-hung windows 
 operate and how they can be repaired\, including basic glass pane 
 replacement.\n\nThe workshop will also introduce the basics of residential 
 wiring\, demonstrating how outlets and lighting are installed and 
 connected. Throughout the session\, Robert will answer questions and offer 
 guidance on a wide range of home repair topics.\n\nWhether you're a 
 homeowner looking to handle basic repairs yourself or simply curious about 
 how things in your home work\, this class provides practical knowledge you 
 can use right away.\n
LOCATION:Montclair - Montclair High School\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Arts & Crafts
UID:LibCal-10306-16502636
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16502636
END:VEVENT
