LAST-MODIFIED:20260330T150112Z
UID:10007126-1776504600-1776508200@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Mindfulness in the Garden (Weekend Classes)
DESCRIPTION:Mindfulness in the Garden (Weekend Classes) \nSaturdays\, 9:30 AM – 10:30 AM \nApril 18th \nMay 9th \nJune 13th \nInstructor: Jodi Brooks \nDiscover how a mindfulness practice can help us awaken and  live in harmony with oneself and with the natural world. Each class will include: simple instructions for getting started with a formal mindfulness practice\, very gentle stretching & breathwork\, and an outdoor contemplative garden walk. This is a practice of slowing down\, cultivating quiet and paying attention to our senses. All levels are welcome. No experience needed. Cold or rainy weather – class will be held indoors\, with a short walk outdoors (weather permitting). \nFee per class:  $20 Members / $25 General Public \nPre Registration is required.  There are no drop-ins for this class.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/mindfulness-in-the-garden-weekend-classes/2026-04-18/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/02/Mindfulness-8-e1771345155277.jpg
END:VEVENT
