DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260419T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260419T150000
DTSTAMP:20260401T003536
CREATED:20260109T214103Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T154714Z
UID:10006032-1776607200-1776610800@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Second Sunday Concert - Cart & Marrazza (rescheduled date)
DESCRIPTION:Rescheduled from December\, 2025 due to snowstorm. The previous reservations for this performance will be honored. Unclaimed seats will be available right before the start of the concert. There is no waitlist. \n  \nNow April 19\, 2026 – Marrazza-Cart Duo \nHOPE WILL NEVER BE SILENT \nRobert Cart\, flutist\, and Regina DiMedio-Marrazza\, piano\, are a chamber ensemble\, renowned for\npassionate and musically stirring performances throughout the United States\, including concerts at Carnegie Hall\, the Kennedy Center\, the Philadelphia Ethical Society\, the Philadelphia International Music Festival\, the National Flute Association\, and several colleges and universities. The duo has premiered new works by Jennifer Higdon and Gary Schocker. Advocates of new music\, they have also premiered new works by Louis Barroso\, Jennifer Higdon\, and Gary Schocker. They have graced our stage at Van Vleck House many times and are a series favorite with concert-goers. \nAll Second Sunday concerts begin at 2PM. Seats are limited and reservations are recommended. If registered guests do not attend\, those seats will be open to visitors right before the start of the concert.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/cart-marrazza-rescheduled/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Events,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2022/08/marrazza-cart-duo.jpg
END:VEVENT
