X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Foundation": "https://montclairfoundation.org/event/virtual-meditation-31-9/2026-04-22/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairfoundation_calendar_of_events
X-SOURCE:Montclair Foundation
X-SOURCE-URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T210000
DTSTAMP:20260401T003536
CREATED:20260318T225001Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260318T225002Z
UID:10006014-1776884400-1776891600@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Virtual Meditation
DESCRIPTION:Virtual Meditation \nInstructor: John Welshons \nWednesdays\, 7:00 PM – 9:00 PM \nJanuary 7\, 14\, 21\, 28 \nFebruary 4\, 11\, 25 \nMarch 4\, 18\, 25 \nApril 1\, 8\, 15\, 22\, 29 \nMay 6\, 13\, 20 \nJune 3\, 10\, 24 \nJoin contemporary spiritual teacher and author Ramananda John E. Welshons (One Soul\, One Love\, One Heart\, When Prayers Aren’t Answered and Awakening From Grief) for a series of evening meditation classes in the comfort of your own home via Zoom. These classes will focus on specific practices for working with fear and anxiety.  Participants will learn and practice different forms of mindfulness meditation in each session and will have the opportunity to participate in discussions of Ramananda’s three critically acclaimed books. Open to beginners and experienced practitioners\, these gatherings offer an opportunity to experience deep inner peace while practicing with a highly experienced meditation teacher.  \nImportant Updated Registration Information: \nA Zoom Link will be sent the day of the class. If you are registering after 3 PM on the day of the class\, the Zoom link will be included in the automated payment confirmation email sent when you register. There is no registration deadline for this class. \nFee: Single class: $10 Members / $15 General Public
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/virtual-meditation-31-9/2026-04-22/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults,Virtual
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2024/06/outdoor-meditation-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northeast Earth Coalition": "https://neearth.org/events/movie-screening-the-little-things-that-run-the-world-earth-week-celebration/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:neearth
X-SOURCE:Northeast Earth Coalition
X-SOURCE-URL:https://neearth.org/events/
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T210000
DTSTAMP:20260401T003547
CREATED:20260224T201232Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T184151Z
UID:3268-1776884400-1776891600@neearth.org
SUMMARY:Movie screening: "The Little Things That Run the World" - Earth Week Celebration
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a screening of “The Little Things That Run the World\,” part of our Bee City USA program. \nSynopsis:\nLife on Earth is in the middle of a major re-alignment of species composition. The smallest of creatures – insects – hold the fabric of all life together. They are the most numerous of all animal groups on the planet. But insects are declining at an alarming rate throughout the world\, threatening innumerable species\, whole ecosystems\, and even our food systems with collapse. This is story about untangling the mysteries as to why something so ubiquitous – and seemingly endless – could be on the cusp of disappearing entirely. It is also the story of heroic efforts to save these most vulnerable of creatures. \nAdmission is free. Register to save your seat. \nLearn more about the film here. \n 
URL:https://neearth.org/events/movie-screening-the-little-things-that-run-the-world-earth-week-celebration/
LOCATION:Guild Room at First Congregational Church\, 40 South Fullerton Avenue\, Montclair\, New Jersey\, 07042\, 07042\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://neearth.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/little-things-that-run-the-world.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Northeast Earth Coalition":MAILTO:info@neearth.org
END:VEVENT
