SUMMARY:Cultural ARTS Series: Allison Loggins - Hull and NJS
DESCRIPTION:Cultural ARTS Series – New Jersey Symphony String Quartet with Allison Loggins-Hull \nApril 25\, 7:30 PM \nFeaturing the music of NJS Resident Artistic Partner and Montclair resident Allison Loggins-Hull\, who is known for her genre-bending work as a flutist\, composer\, and producer. Don’t miss this special experience! \nAllison Loggins-Hull: Homeland for solo flute • Florence Price: String Quartet in G Major • Allison Loggins-Hull: Ban • Dvorak: String Quartet No. 12 “American” \nTickets are required and include refreshments.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/cultural-arts-series-allison-loggins-hull-and-njs/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Events,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/02/allison-loggins-hull-by-rafael-rios.webp
END:VEVENT
