BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ics Kstx8Swyw669Kakgqa 6478083 Ics": "https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2025222010"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ics_kstx8swyw669kakgqa_6478083_ics
SUMMARY:Jewish without Apology: A Conversation with Sarah Hurwitz
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T170000
DTSTAMP:20260328T020314Z
UID:TU2025222010
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T150000
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260115T234631Z
DESCRIPTION:**Seth Goodchild Memorial Lecture**  \nReception immediately f
 ollowing  \n  \nRSVP: http://shomrei.org/hurwitz  \n  \n**About the Progra
 m**  \nAward-winning author Sarah Hurwitz joins Rabbi Julie Roth for a can
 did conversation about rediscovering Judaism as an adult and why its intel
 lectual depth and moral clarity feel strikingly relevant to modern life. F
 rom finding meaning in a chaotic world to standing tall against rising ant
 isemitism\, Sarah explores why embracing Jewish wisdom isn’t just about 
 honoring the past -- it’s about sanctifying the present and elevating ou
 r shared humanity.   \n  \n**Free Babysitting Available**  \nEmail Aviva A
 rad\, aarad@shomrei.org  \n  \n**\\*Additional parking is available next d
 oor at 73 &amp\; 77 Park Street.**  \n  \n**In Loving Memory of Seth Goodc
 hild**   \nSeth Goodchild was inspired by his family to convert to Judaism
  at the end of his life. To honor his legacy and share his love of Judaism
 \, his friends and family sponsored this lecture and a class on exploring 
 Judaism.\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20260327T203605Z
TRANSP:OPAQUE
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2025222010
X-SOURCE:Congregation Shomrei Emunah
X-SOURCE-URL:https://shomrei.org/calendar/
END:VEVENT
