BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-ID:gcal_id8bbkkkfmscdavi2jilkb2muo
SUMMARY:Weekly Labyrinth Walks\, Wednesdays 11am-1pm
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260429T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260429T130000
DTSTAMP:20260401T043557Z
UID:ludgoqjjiam6rn46dm98mt3a9e@google.com__20260429
SEQUENCE:1
CREATED:20240529T134031Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><span>Weekly: Wednesdays 11am-1pm in the Sanctuary</spa
 n><span> </span><span></span><i> </i><p></p><p><span>Take your soul for a 
 walk on the labyrinth.  We are pleased to offer labyrinth walks each Wedn
 esday in the mid-day as a chance to connect with your soul in our beautifu
 l sanctuary. <br><br>The labyrinth is an ancient spiritual tool \, a mode
  of “walking prayer” that invites us to go deeper in our walk with God
 .  Our labyrinth\, modeled on one in Chartes Cathedral in France\, sits a
 s the center of our Sanctuary\, a constant metaphor for our spiritual live
 s.  Just like the labyrinth\, our lives are not linear\, but filled with 
 twists and turns.  Sometimes we make great progress\, and other times we 
 feel we are going backwards.  But if we trust in the path we will find ou
 rselves in the center -- the heart of God.</span> <br></p><p><span>All are
  welcome to take their souls out for a healing walk... no experience neces
 sary! </span> <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://baristanet.co
 m/2014/03/labyrinth-walk-meditation-satisfies-soul/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=
 calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0Y_UBYHduSYmZAtn0VUHmP" target="_blank"
 ><span>Check out this lovely write up on Baristanet</span></a> <span>from 
 the Spring 2014.</span> <br></p><p><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=h
 ttps://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue%3D2%26v%3DD453ajtWb74%26feature
 %3Demb_logo&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0jnAO
 _0I_l5nW8Ob7EnbtQ" target="_blank"><span>Watch this video</span></a> <span
 >to find out more about walking the labyrinth. If you’ve never done so c
 ome out one Wednesday evening and give it a try. It is a wonderful way to 
 nourish your soul and spend some quiet time in prayer or meditation.</span
 ></p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251215T182737Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-SOURCE:First Congregational Church Montclair
X-SOURCE-URL:https://fccmontclair.org/upcoming-events-at-fcc/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Campuslabs Montclair": "https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313"}
X-SOURCE-ID:campuslabs_montclair
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Social
CATEGORIES:Large Scale
DESCRIPTION:April is Sexual Assault Awareness Month\, and together\, we ca
 n break the silence. The Montclair State University Police Department and
  the Office of Advocacy & Outreach are committed to fostering a campus wh
 ere survivors feel heard\, supported\, and empowered. It starts with beli
 eving. It starts with you. By offering a safe and affirming response to t
 hose who disclose gender-based and sexual violence\, we can create lastin
 g change. Let’s stand together to end the cycle of silence—because every 
 voice matters\, and every action counts.\nDenim Day is recognized interna
 tionally as a day of action and awareness\, encouraging people to wear de
 nim to challenge victim-blaming and educate others about sexual violence.
  This year\, Denim Day falls on Wednesday\, April 29\, 2026.\nThe Univers
 ity Police and Office of Advocacy & Outreach and the Office of Advocacy a
 nd Community Resilience\, in partnership with over 30 campus and local co
 mmunity organizations\, invites you to join us from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. at 
 the Amphitheater for a powerful awareness event honoring survivors and in
 creasing awareness of available resources.\nDespite the gaps that still e
 xist in the criminal justice system\, in resources\, and in prevention ed
 ucation\, we will move forward together as a community. As part of this c
 ommitment\, we will walk one mile around campus in solidarity with surviv
 ors.\n\nHosted by: Advocacy and Outreach\n\nAdditional Information can be
  found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
DTEND:20260429T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260401T043556Z
DTSTART:20260429T130000Z
LOCATION:Amphitheater
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Denim Day 2026: Mind the Gaps\, Move Forward
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11871313
X-HOSTS:Advocacy and Outreach
END:VEVENT
